{
  "texts": [
    "The weighted cell-level predictions are aggregated to generate the polling estimates.",
    "Beyond the sample, a number of selected auxiliary variables obtained via linkage with publicly available datasets are used to inform both the generalisation of the sample and the generated weights.",
    "(2) Non-parametric models: these are models characterised by an undefined set of parameters, the number of which tends to grow according to the size and complexity of the underlying sample.",
    "Unlike for parametric models, the parameters of these algorithms are uninterpretable.",
    "The parameters cannot be compared across models fit to different samples, as the same model will learn different latent structures from the data depending on the features of the specific sample."
  ]
}